   "source": [
    "## Imports and dataset loading\n",
    "\n",
    "This cell imports required libraries and loads the Fashion-MNIST dataset from Keras.\n",
    "It also reshapes the data to the shape expected by Conv2D (`(samples, 28, 28, 1)`)\n",
    "and scales pixel values to the range `[0, 1]` by dividing by 255.\n",
    "\n",
    "Notes:\n",
    "- We keep labels as integer class IDs and use `sparse_categorical_crossentropy` later.\n",
    "- If you run on GPU, TensorFlow will automatically use it if available.\n",
    "- `%matplotlib inline` is used for notebooks so plots appear inline."
